WEBVTT

00:53.386 --> 00:54.596
It's clean.

00:55.305 --> 00:57.015
It's perfect
for a single-person household.

01:00.477 --> 01:02.854
Someone else also saw this place
this morning.

01:02.937 --> 01:04.272
The client liked it very much

01:04.355 --> 01:06.149
and wanted to sign
a provisional agreement.

01:07.192 --> 01:09.152
There's some time left for you to decide.

01:10.278 --> 01:11.279
I see.

01:14.365 --> 01:16.159
I'll take this place.

01:16.868 --> 01:17.911
Will you?

01:18.119 --> 01:21.414
Then would you like to sign the lease
right away?

01:25.084 --> 01:26.169
Yes, let's do that.

01:32.842 --> 01:34.344
Please excuse me for a moment.

01:39.224 --> 01:40.099
Hey.

01:40.475 --> 01:41.476
Where are you?

01:43.144 --> 01:44.395
I'm at the store now.

01:45.146 --> 01:46.272
When will you be done?

01:48.399 --> 01:49.567
I'm not sure.

01:52.320 --> 01:54.072
- Why do you ask?
- Because of my business trip.

01:55.031 --> 01:56.366
I have to leave tomorrow.

01:56.741 --> 01:58.034
I want to see you before I leave.

01:58.618 --> 01:59.619
Oh, I see.

02:00.870 --> 02:02.122
What's with that reaction?

02:04.415 --> 02:07.585
I was just thinking about
which restaurant I should take you.

02:07.669 --> 02:09.379
I should take you to somewhere nice.

02:10.004 --> 02:11.089
Are you my mom or what?

02:12.215 --> 02:13.258
No, I'm your girlfriend.

02:29.399 --> 02:30.692
Did I make you wait for too long?

02:31.568 --> 02:33.570
You said you were almost here,
so I already ordered.

02:33.653 --> 02:35.155
Okay. Great.

02:41.077 --> 02:44.164
Were you busy?
You didn't text me at all today.

02:44.706 --> 02:47.584
Yes, I had a hectic day today.

02:48.626 --> 02:50.879
I hope you stay busy
while I'm on my business trip.

02:51.671 --> 02:52.589
Why?

02:54.465 --> 02:56.175
Then you can take your mind off
other things.

02:57.677 --> 02:59.929
What do you mean by that?

03:00.638 --> 03:04.392
I just don't want you to worry too much
about having to move out.

03:05.476 --> 03:07.687
Let's sort things out when I come back.

03:09.898 --> 03:11.733
I said I don't need anything else.

03:13.067 --> 03:15.528
I don't want you to feel pressured
to do something for me.

03:17.572 --> 03:19.532
It's not that I feel pressured. I want to.

03:20.241 --> 03:22.744
For you, I want to do everything I can.

04:24.514 --> 04:27.684
Have you ever thought about quitting work?

04:30.687 --> 04:32.355
Why all of a sudden?

04:36.734 --> 04:38.987
I was going to tell you after I come back.

04:39.821 --> 04:42.115
Actually, I applied
to go work at the US branch.

04:46.160 --> 04:47.620
I don't know the exact date yet,

04:47.787 --> 04:50.206
but I'll go there by the end of this year
at the latest.

04:51.499 --> 04:54.168
Are you asking me to quit my job
and go with you?

04:59.215 --> 05:01.384
I think that'll be for the best.

05:02.844 --> 05:04.053
How exactly?

05:06.014 --> 05:07.307
I know it's quite sudden.

05:11.144 --> 05:12.562
Are you saying we should run away?

05:17.734 --> 05:19.694
I'd rather have you say
that we're breaking free.

05:24.407 --> 05:26.492
I'm fine with everything as it is.

05:28.494 --> 05:29.370
I'm not.

05:30.580 --> 05:32.332
Why do we have to go so far away?

05:32.415 --> 05:34.208
We can just live together here.

05:34.292 --> 05:35.293
You said that was crazy.

05:36.169 --> 05:37.628
And going to the States isn't?

05:39.422 --> 05:41.132
You said all you needed was me.

05:41.716 --> 05:42.842
Yes, I did.

05:44.427 --> 05:47.221
But that also means that I'm satisfied
with where we are now.

05:47.305 --> 05:48.514
Not for me.

05:51.309 --> 05:54.771
Everyone's tormenting you,
and I can no longer watch you suffer.

06:41.609 --> 06:44.153
Let's talk about it again
when I come back from my business trip.

06:46.280 --> 06:47.156
Okay.

06:57.208 --> 07:00.211
Don't keep it all to yourself
and stress yourself out.

07:01.629 --> 07:03.131
Be good while I'm gone.

07:03.798 --> 07:04.799
Okay.

07:05.383 --> 07:06.634
Have a safe trip.

07:08.261 --> 07:09.262
Bye.

07:15.601 --> 07:16.561
Bye.

08:10.448 --> 08:14.494
LEASE AGREEMENT

09:20.017 --> 09:21.060
Hello.

09:22.520 --> 09:23.479
Hello.

09:25.398 --> 09:26.691
Good morning.

09:27.483 --> 09:28.526
Hello.

10:23.664 --> 10:24.957
Hey, Gyeong-seon.

10:37.928 --> 10:40.890
I know this may sound like

10:41.766 --> 10:43.559
I'm blaming everything on Jun-hui.

10:45.186 --> 10:47.438
I think Jun-hui got a little impatient

10:48.022 --> 10:50.232
because of the situation I'm in.

10:50.858 --> 10:52.401
He made a rash decision.

10:52.985 --> 10:55.488
I don't think he thought it through.

10:55.571 --> 10:57.740
He's not that thoughtless.

10:58.449 --> 11:01.285
He wouldn't have discussed it with me
if it was a rash decision.

11:01.577 --> 11:04.205
He would've gone straight to the realtor
and list his place for sale.

11:05.915 --> 11:07.708
What are you guys planning to do?

11:09.669 --> 11:11.545
I know me saying this might upset you,

11:12.922 --> 11:14.548
but don't think that I'm with him on this.

11:15.841 --> 11:17.468
Are you saying Jun-hui is the only one

11:18.010 --> 11:19.887
who's desperate about living together?

11:21.514 --> 11:23.682
I'm pretty sure
I'm more desperate than he is.

11:31.065 --> 11:32.441
To be honest,

11:34.151 --> 11:36.946
I don't care
what my parents or you might say

11:37.863 --> 11:39.698
or do to me.

11:40.366 --> 11:41.450
I can put up with anything.

11:43.285 --> 11:44.995
I would like to do

11:45.955 --> 11:49.166
as Jun-hui suggests
without considering anything else.

11:51.544 --> 11:53.129
I even thought to myself

11:54.922 --> 11:57.174
that I might be able to dodge the blame

11:58.676 --> 12:00.177
if I hid behind Jun-hui.

12:07.101 --> 12:08.185
But...

12:11.272 --> 12:13.649
I think I'm more selfish than I thought.

12:16.277 --> 12:17.570
I keep saying

12:18.362 --> 12:20.322
that I don't want Jun-hui to get blamed

12:20.406 --> 12:22.783
as if that is why I'm being hesitant.

12:24.118 --> 12:26.036
But to be honest,
I'm only pursuing what I want.

12:27.997 --> 12:29.999
I still have a lot of things
that I want to do.

12:33.961 --> 12:35.129
I won't give up on everything

12:36.046 --> 12:37.715
just to be with Jun-hui.

12:42.678 --> 12:44.889
I will date him like how I've been doing

12:46.515 --> 12:50.060
and carry on with the things
that I must do and want to do.

12:59.904 --> 13:02.740
Should I thank you or hate you?

13:07.161 --> 13:08.204
I'm sorry.

13:10.289 --> 13:11.874
This is who I am.

13:16.086 --> 13:17.588
Look me in the eye.

13:23.469 --> 13:26.555
Have you changed
or have you always been like this?

13:33.312 --> 13:34.813
Whatever it is,

13:36.065 --> 13:38.984
I would appreciate it
if you could think positively about it.

13:47.159 --> 13:49.203
I have right
to be disappointed in you, right?

13:54.083 --> 13:55.167
Is it that bad?

13:59.755 --> 14:01.423
I can't stand you any longer.

14:06.762 --> 14:08.013
You said it yourself

14:09.098 --> 14:11.058
that you put yourself before Jun-hui.

14:12.268 --> 14:13.686
Keep your word.

17:01.353 --> 17:03.647
- Please leave the door open.
- Okay.

17:28.005 --> 17:29.882
- Hi.
- It's me.

17:31.383 --> 17:32.384
Hey.

17:32.718 --> 17:34.303
Why do you still sound so down?

17:34.803 --> 17:36.263
You don't sound that cheerful either.

17:37.431 --> 17:39.558
It's your day off. What are you up to?

17:41.935 --> 17:44.229
Nothing special.

17:45.147 --> 17:46.607
You can't wait to see me, right?

17:47.941 --> 17:49.193
I'm doing just fine without you.

17:50.152 --> 17:51.862
I'm dying to see you.

17:54.782 --> 17:55.783
We're almost done.

17:57.868 --> 17:59.787
- Who was that?
- Hang on a second.

18:00.871 --> 18:02.831
I'll be down in a minute.

18:06.293 --> 18:07.294
Hey.

18:08.003 --> 18:09.129
Is someone at your place?

18:10.214 --> 18:13.217
Yes, someone is here
to repair the water purifier.

18:14.009 --> 18:15.094
I see.

18:15.928 --> 18:17.304
I have to get back to the meeting.

18:17.596 --> 18:20.265
- I'll call you later.
- Okay, bye.

18:39.952 --> 18:41.912
I set the table. Come on.

18:44.498 --> 18:45.874
Are you going to starve yourself?

18:49.378 --> 18:50.754
Why did you kick her out

18:50.838 --> 18:52.840
if you were going to worry like this?

18:54.550 --> 18:56.552
No parent can persuade a determined child.

18:57.386 --> 18:58.595
Shut the door.

19:01.181 --> 19:02.391
Goodness.

19:08.313 --> 19:10.440
Gosh, this is frustrating.

19:45.309 --> 19:46.393
I can't believe this.

19:47.436 --> 19:48.896
Did Jin-a really move out?

19:50.480 --> 19:52.191
Take a seat if you haven't eaten already.

19:54.651 --> 19:56.028
What about Mom?

19:57.279 --> 19:58.572
She said she doesn't want to eat.

20:05.829 --> 20:06.872
Did you...

20:08.123 --> 20:10.751
hear anything from Jun-hui?

20:11.460 --> 20:12.502
Like what?

20:13.170 --> 20:15.255
All I heard is that he's in China
for a business trip.

20:17.466 --> 20:18.592
Oh, about Jin-a moving out.

20:20.427 --> 20:22.262
Maybe Jin-a didn't even tell him about it.

20:27.559 --> 20:29.561
I thought it was weird
that she was rushing it.

20:30.604 --> 20:32.522
She caused trouble again.

20:34.149 --> 20:35.609
My gosh.

20:38.445 --> 20:42.074
Don't mention anything
about it to Jun-hui.

20:42.658 --> 20:44.159
I won't even if you ask me to.

20:44.409 --> 20:46.078
He'll fly home right away if he finds out.

20:49.456 --> 20:50.457
But Dad,

20:51.291 --> 20:53.460
you should do something about Mom.

20:54.211 --> 20:56.505
Provoking them won't solve anything.

20:57.381 --> 20:59.841
He doesn't really show it,

20:59.925 --> 21:01.343
but Jun-hui has a huge ego.

21:02.302 --> 21:04.221
He doesn't let anyone mess with him,

21:04.471 --> 21:07.015
but he's putting up with this
because it's us.

21:08.433 --> 21:10.143
But how long do you think that will last?

21:10.227 --> 21:11.687
He can only take so much.

21:24.449 --> 21:26.785
You've got so much stuff
for a person living alone.

21:28.745 --> 21:29.830
I know.

21:30.664 --> 21:33.333
I'm putting you through so much trouble
on your day off.

21:33.417 --> 21:36.712
I'll buy you a really nice meal
when we get the next paycheck.

21:37.796 --> 21:39.131
You've got a long way to go.

21:39.798 --> 21:41.758
Aren't you forgetting
about your rent, water bills,

21:42.134 --> 21:44.594
electricity bills, gas bills,
and all the other bills?

21:46.263 --> 21:48.724
- I already feel suffocated.
- Already?

21:50.017 --> 21:51.059
What are you trying to say?

21:52.060 --> 21:54.980
Your job, your family, and Jun-hui...

21:55.897 --> 21:56.857
Gosh.

21:57.399 --> 21:59.443
Just eat.

22:02.195 --> 22:03.655
Are you sure about this?

22:07.951 --> 22:09.286
I have to be even if I'm not.

22:12.331 --> 22:13.582
I like that attitude.

22:15.584 --> 22:17.419
You'll need it to survive.

22:20.714 --> 22:21.590
Right.

22:48.533 --> 22:50.702
- That's good. You did a great job.
- Thanks.

22:50.786 --> 22:53.413
The legal team will have
a separate meeting with Yoon Jin-a.

22:54.289 --> 22:55.749
- That's a relief.
- Right.

22:56.833 --> 22:57.918
By the way,

22:58.794 --> 23:00.462
what are you planning to do with Mr. Kong?

23:04.174 --> 23:05.717
- You see,
- Yes.

23:05.884 --> 23:09.387
nothing is completely over
until you tie up all the loose ends.

23:09.721 --> 23:10.889
- You know what I mean.
- I do.

23:14.267 --> 23:16.895
As soon as things get wrapped up,
I will...

23:18.146 --> 23:19.523
You know.

23:23.318 --> 23:25.278
It's about time you get a promotion.

23:28.698 --> 23:30.367
You shouldn't be stuck in one position.

23:30.700 --> 23:32.619
- Right.
- Even when you work,

23:33.120 --> 23:34.329
you know...

23:35.413 --> 23:36.957
Dragging things out will only get you...

23:37.749 --> 23:39.000
You know.

23:40.418 --> 23:42.337
I'll take care of it
as soon as possible, sir.

23:45.423 --> 23:48.093
I know you feel responsible
as you represent all the female employees,

23:48.718 --> 23:50.887
but no one will benefit
if the word gets out.

23:52.347 --> 23:54.182
The company's reputation matters, too.

23:55.517 --> 23:56.768
I am aware of that, sir.

23:57.686 --> 23:59.521
I think we must follow
the proper procedures

23:59.604 --> 24:02.524
and reprimand those who are responsible
to protect the company's reputation.

24:02.607 --> 24:04.401
We'll set up a fact-finding committee.

24:04.484 --> 24:06.444
After Mr. Nam gets out of it?

24:12.117 --> 24:14.035
Are you trying to put
our reputation at risk?

24:14.703 --> 24:18.331
Will you be satisfied
once you bring the whole company down?

24:19.583 --> 24:21.668
We have to find a way
to minimize the risks.

24:22.711 --> 24:25.088
We can't let this small issue
jeopardize our company's future.

24:25.964 --> 24:29.342
As a general manager, you must know
how to deal with matters objectively!

24:31.011 --> 24:32.762
Stop going over the line.

24:33.972 --> 24:36.975
I didn't give you that position so that
you can side with the female employees.

24:38.852 --> 24:39.895
Jeong Yeong-in.

24:40.937 --> 24:42.189
Come to your senses.

24:46.484 --> 24:47.736
Just get it over with.

24:47.861 --> 24:50.280
Suck it up and apologize publicly.

24:50.363 --> 24:51.865
It's easier said than done.

24:52.616 --> 24:53.617
Listen,

24:54.201 --> 24:56.244
things might get out of hand

24:56.328 --> 24:57.495
after the committee is set up.

24:57.579 --> 24:59.164
Do you want to end up in court?

24:59.247 --> 25:01.958
There are many things that I can use
as evidence. I feel victimized.

25:02.042 --> 25:03.668
Think about your family first.

25:04.544 --> 25:07.756
Suck it up just this once.
Would you rather lose your job?

25:10.717 --> 25:13.511
Even if I apologize publicly,

25:14.346 --> 25:15.680
I'll still be reprimanded.

25:17.015 --> 25:18.558
Hey, listen.

25:18.767 --> 25:21.937
If you handle it quietly,
at least you won't lose your job.

25:22.562 --> 25:24.064
They'll move you to a team

25:24.147 --> 25:25.857
where you won't have to work
with Yoon Jin-a.

25:25.941 --> 25:29.653
If that doesn't happen, I'll talk
to the management on your behalf.

25:32.322 --> 25:34.324
You seem to care a lot about this issue

25:34.407 --> 25:36.618
when you rarely get involved
with other people's business.

25:38.662 --> 25:41.456
Hey, it's because
you vent to me all the time.

25:41.539 --> 25:43.041
If you want me to stop caring, I will.

25:43.124 --> 25:46.795
No, don't be like this.
I'm seriously going nuts!

25:57.514 --> 25:58.932
You can get this through.

26:15.198 --> 26:17.617
I'm from the law firm
that takes care of the company's--

26:17.701 --> 26:19.411
You already told me over the phone.

26:23.915 --> 26:27.043
I wasn't sure what you'd like,
so I ordered both coffee and tea.

26:28.044 --> 26:30.338
- I'll have the tea.
- Sure.

26:32.799 --> 26:34.426
I asked you to meet with me because...

26:35.010 --> 26:36.594
You probably know already,

26:37.345 --> 26:39.889
but I'd like to talk to you
about the sexual harassment issue.

26:40.640 --> 26:42.267
I've already told the management

26:42.350 --> 26:44.185
that I want the assailants
to apologize publicly

26:44.269 --> 26:45.854
and receive proper disciplinary action.

26:46.563 --> 26:50.358
I am not seeking any form of settlement

26:50.442 --> 26:51.651
or mediation.

26:52.277 --> 26:53.111
Hang on a second.

26:55.739 --> 26:57.073
Why do you call them "assailants"?

26:58.116 --> 27:01.119
We haven't concluded
that you're the victim in the case.

27:02.412 --> 27:04.414
- Pardon me?
- You must be baffled.

27:05.040 --> 27:07.917
You see, this is just the beginning.

27:11.004 --> 27:15.425
I'm sure you've read about similar cases
on the news.

27:16.634 --> 27:18.970
How did those cases pan out?

27:19.721 --> 27:20.847
Didn't you feel frustrated?

27:21.598 --> 27:24.059
There's no conclusion.
Nothing really comes out of it.

27:26.144 --> 27:27.395
Why do you think that is?

27:30.982 --> 27:32.233
Let me put it in layman's terms.

28:03.556 --> 28:05.141
JIN-A: I HAD A GREAT TIME. GOOD NIGHT.

28:05.308 --> 28:06.142
Well...

28:07.185 --> 28:10.063
When things like this go public,
everyone will say the same thing.

28:12.440 --> 28:15.652
"The woman is partially responsible.
She's actually the one to blame."

28:16.528 --> 28:18.530
Even worse, people will say
you wanted to get--

28:18.613 --> 28:19.447
Hold on.

28:20.156 --> 28:22.492
Where did you get this footage?

28:23.576 --> 28:25.120
Is this the original file?

28:26.496 --> 28:28.498
And these messages...

28:30.417 --> 28:34.129
I've never sent these messages to Mr. Nam.

28:35.755 --> 28:37.799
- I'll show you what I have on my--
- It'll be too late.

28:40.593 --> 28:42.679
What I'm saying is
that you won't be able to reverse

28:42.762 --> 28:44.514
people's negative impression of you.

28:47.767 --> 28:49.894
I can understand how frustrated
you must be

28:50.353 --> 28:52.188
and how unfair all of this is.

28:53.106 --> 28:56.860
But I'd like you to think it over again.

28:57.152 --> 29:00.864
Try to think about what will benefit you.

29:02.532 --> 29:03.658
"Benefit"?

29:05.118 --> 29:07.078
I've already lost too many things.

29:08.872 --> 29:12.292
I got myself into this
knowing that things may get harder.

29:13.501 --> 29:15.962
I see. All right.

29:17.922 --> 29:21.509
Mr. Nam is considering
suing you for defamation.

29:22.719 --> 29:26.097
If you sincerely apologize to him
before he goes ahead with it,

29:27.140 --> 29:28.558
he might change his mind.

29:33.229 --> 29:34.355
Ms. Yoon.

29:38.067 --> 29:39.861
I'm speaking from my experience.

29:40.695 --> 29:44.866
In cases like this, nothing good comes out
of dragging things out.

29:46.117 --> 29:49.287
I'm telling you this
because I feel bad for you.

29:50.663 --> 29:53.249
I feel bad for you.

29:54.542 --> 29:58.046
Did you study hard and become a lawyer
to cook up schemes like this?

29:58.880 --> 30:02.008
Go tell them
that they have underestimated me.

30:02.091 --> 30:04.010
I will never let them have their way.

31:44.736 --> 31:48.072
AIRPORT LIMOUSINE

32:04.297 --> 32:07.300
Are you still at work?
Why aren't you answering my calls?

33:00.019 --> 33:02.063
- Hey.
- Where are you?

33:03.940 --> 33:06.651
- I'm home.
- Then why didn't you pick up the phone?

33:09.237 --> 33:10.238
What is it?

33:10.738 --> 33:11.864
Is Jun-hui there?

33:14.826 --> 33:17.412
- What?
- He called me.

33:17.495 --> 33:18.997
He said he couldn't reach you.

33:19.080 --> 33:21.874
He was as agitated as he was
back when you had gotten into an accident.

33:23.042 --> 33:25.753
- So, what did you say?
- We talked for a bit,

33:26.170 --> 33:28.131
and I ended up telling him
that you moved out.

33:28.965 --> 33:29.966
Hey.

33:43.146 --> 33:44.147
You're back.

33:48.818 --> 33:49.944
I guess you didn't get lost.

33:54.991 --> 33:56.034
Come in.

34:09.839 --> 34:11.966
You didn't eat yet, did you?

34:12.091 --> 34:13.176
I only have ramyeon.

34:14.260 --> 34:15.845
Or maybe not.

34:17.180 --> 34:20.016
Let's go get something to eat.
I haven't had dinner yet.

34:21.184 --> 34:22.727
I want to talk first.

34:24.520 --> 34:25.521
Okay.

34:27.065 --> 34:28.983
Take a seat.

34:32.445 --> 34:33.446
I'll just sit here.

34:49.295 --> 34:51.631
I don't have a table yet.

34:52.131 --> 34:54.133
- We can use this--
- It's fine.

34:57.386 --> 34:59.263
Right, I do have a tray.

35:00.973 --> 35:03.768
I don't cook at home,

35:04.393 --> 35:07.313
so I haven't even unpacked
the kitchenware.

35:11.567 --> 35:12.902
I thought you'd be back tomorrow.

35:15.029 --> 35:16.322
Things ended a day earlier.

35:17.281 --> 35:20.326
If you told me earlier,
I would've gone to the airport to--

35:20.409 --> 35:21.577
Why didn't you tell me?

35:23.788 --> 35:25.206
Because you didn't want to worry me?

35:28.292 --> 35:30.753
I know you'll think
that I always use the same excuse,

35:30.837 --> 35:32.004
but that really is the reason.

35:32.088 --> 35:34.048
We agreed to talk about it
after I come back.

35:35.174 --> 35:36.467
Why were you in such a rush?

35:39.303 --> 35:41.347
I was only gone for a week.
What was so urgent?

35:44.183 --> 35:45.476
Then what about you?

35:47.645 --> 35:49.564
I heard you were going to sell your place.

35:52.066 --> 35:53.442
I told you I'm going to the States.

35:54.318 --> 35:55.695
Do you think I don't know you?

35:56.195 --> 35:58.447
You were trying
to help me out financially.

35:59.031 --> 36:00.908
- Am I wrong?
- What's wrong with that?

36:01.909 --> 36:03.578
I'm going to do everything I can do
for you.

36:04.662 --> 36:05.997
What would that make me look like?

36:07.456 --> 36:09.250
I worry about
how Gyeong-seon would think of me

36:10.001 --> 36:13.212
as much as you worry about
how my mom would think of you.

36:14.213 --> 36:16.215
I don't want to disappoint her anymore.

36:17.091 --> 36:18.467
I can't do that.

36:20.595 --> 36:21.804
Then what about me?

36:22.847 --> 36:24.390
Do you expect me to do nothing?

36:26.184 --> 36:27.476
What am I to you?

36:28.352 --> 36:29.854
Am I just a convenience to you?

36:31.647 --> 36:34.609
- Why would you say that?
- You're making me think that way.

36:38.905 --> 36:40.656
It's not like
you have to do something for me.

36:42.241 --> 36:45.411
Can't we just love and support each other?

36:46.037 --> 36:47.121
And what's that going to do?

36:48.331 --> 36:51.292
Do you think we'll live happily ever after

36:52.168 --> 36:53.461
if we keep enduring everything?

36:56.088 --> 36:58.132
There's no need to be sarcastic.

37:01.135 --> 37:02.929
I can't keep living like this.

37:08.059 --> 37:09.143
What do you mean?

37:11.062 --> 37:13.606
Those people who expect us
to give up on our own...

37:14.315 --> 37:15.399
I can't stand them anymore.

37:18.527 --> 37:20.863
Let's not think too negatively.

37:20.947 --> 37:23.324
Let's be calm
and give it another thought--

37:23.407 --> 37:24.617
I already made up my mind.

39:51.680 --> 39:53.808
This has never happened at your store.

39:54.725 --> 39:57.770
I found a few ingredients
that were expired,

39:57.853 --> 39:59.522
so I took them out.

40:01.565 --> 40:03.401
I forgot to take them out.

40:05.569 --> 40:07.947
Is something worrying you?

40:09.323 --> 40:11.784
Can you make it go away if I tell you?

40:12.368 --> 40:13.327
Go ahead and tell me.

40:13.577 --> 40:15.746
If it's regarding the store,
I'll help you out

40:15.830 --> 40:17.206
in every way I can.

40:18.499 --> 40:20.876
The store always runs systematically,
so it's fine.

40:22.044 --> 40:23.712
Your drink will get cold. Drink up.

40:24.547 --> 40:26.173
I'll try to come up
with a promotional idea

40:26.257 --> 40:28.384
so that we can brighten up the mood.

40:28.759 --> 40:31.762
Things aren't going so well
at the company right now,

40:32.471 --> 40:33.848
so it'll take a while.

40:34.473 --> 40:35.558
Is there something wrong?

40:37.852 --> 40:39.395
There are some things going on.

40:40.980 --> 40:43.399
Do you not meet up with Jin-a
as often these days?

40:44.650 --> 40:46.819
Did you lose your best friend
to your brother?

41:02.543 --> 41:03.919
What's this?

41:04.378 --> 41:06.213
We're both grown-ups.

41:06.714 --> 41:07.882
We're not kids.

41:09.758 --> 41:10.801
That's exactly why.

41:12.428 --> 41:15.556
I started this so that you can realize
what you should

41:15.639 --> 41:17.975
and should not do as a grown-up.

41:18.559 --> 41:19.810
Must you go this far?

41:22.563 --> 41:24.523
I guess you're not ready yet.

41:25.024 --> 41:26.233
I have three kids.

41:29.820 --> 41:32.156
My youngest daughter
is still in kindergarten.

41:32.698 --> 41:36.327
It's natural to make mistakes
once in a while as you work.

41:37.536 --> 41:40.164
If I get fired, it won't just end with me.

41:40.247 --> 41:42.666
That'll be it for my entire family.

41:43.834 --> 41:45.628
If you were so worried about that,

41:45.711 --> 41:48.631
why were you so enthusiastic
about things outside of work?

41:50.758 --> 41:53.928
How would you feel
if your youngest daughter

41:54.762 --> 41:56.972
goes through the same thing
I went through?

41:57.056 --> 41:58.599
Watch your goddamn mouth!

42:10.819 --> 42:12.696
Do you want to know why I'm doing this?

42:14.406 --> 42:16.575
I don't want to be a shameful daughter.

42:18.577 --> 42:21.997
Because my father has never done anything
to be ashamed of.

42:26.293 --> 42:28.837
I made a mistake.

42:31.632 --> 42:34.176
Fine, I'll apologize.

42:38.722 --> 42:40.891
I'm sorry, all right? I'm sorry.

42:44.895 --> 42:45.980
I've wronged you.

42:48.440 --> 42:52.361
I'm really sorry.
I promise it won't happen again.

42:54.863 --> 42:56.073
I'm really sorry.

43:00.411 --> 43:02.663
Please write an apology
on our company notice board.

43:03.289 --> 43:06.375
If you don't,
I'm going to upload this recording file.

43:27.688 --> 43:28.772
Come in.

43:31.817 --> 43:33.027
You wanted to see me?

43:34.945 --> 43:35.946
Have a seat.

43:37.865 --> 43:40.743
If it's going to be brief,
I'd rather listen to you here.

43:43.078 --> 43:44.079
Okay.

43:46.123 --> 43:47.625
I heard you met the attorney.

43:48.834 --> 43:51.754
Ms. Yoon, this isn't something
you should be stubborn about.

43:53.672 --> 43:54.965
I know you are still young,

43:55.716 --> 43:57.760
so I understand you can confuse

43:58.344 --> 43:59.678
recklessness with courage.

44:00.721 --> 44:02.890
I'm not that young or foolish enough

44:03.599 --> 44:06.060
to do something like this
without thinking it through.

44:07.728 --> 44:09.605
If we take this to court, you know,

44:10.022 --> 44:11.690
the odds may be against you.

44:12.900 --> 44:15.861
You might end up with a criminal record.

44:16.528 --> 44:17.529
Is that what you want?

44:18.280 --> 44:20.032
You won't even be able to
get a job elsewhere.

44:21.533 --> 44:23.827
I appreciate your concern.

44:24.787 --> 44:26.789
My gosh, how frustrating.

44:27.164 --> 44:28.123
You know...

44:29.166 --> 44:30.501
Haven't you had enough fun

44:31.001 --> 44:32.294
pretending to be the victim?

44:35.464 --> 44:36.298
So,

44:36.965 --> 44:39.176
are you going to act
like you're the victim now?

44:57.444 --> 44:58.654
I already ate.

44:59.029 --> 45:00.864
I didn't.

45:04.660 --> 45:05.786
Is there something going on?

45:06.578 --> 45:09.540
Can I have the deposit
if your place gets sold?

45:10.624 --> 45:13.127
I want to take a break
without having to worry about money.

45:16.380 --> 45:20.134
You did work all your life
because you had to take care of me.

45:21.635 --> 45:24.138
I didn't say that because I wanted
some acknowledgment from you.

45:25.013 --> 45:28.559
I'm just trying to say
that I need to recharge myself.

45:29.017 --> 45:30.811
I've been running this store
for quite a while.

45:34.189 --> 45:35.149
Is this because of...

45:37.651 --> 45:39.319
Don't jump to conclusions.

45:39.528 --> 45:41.780
This has nothing to do with Jin-a.

45:44.199 --> 45:45.784
Do whatever you want.

45:46.160 --> 45:47.619
You can stay unemployed forever.

45:48.245 --> 45:49.705
I'll take care of you from now on.

45:50.289 --> 45:51.165
Ms. Seo.

45:53.417 --> 45:56.003
I wouldn't let you support me
for the rest of my life.

46:11.727 --> 46:14.188
Yes, we should take that
into consideration.

46:14.688 --> 46:16.857
Okay, I'll call you back.

46:19.193 --> 46:20.694
Did you cast a spell or something?

46:21.111 --> 46:22.154
Pardon?

46:22.529 --> 46:24.490
Mr. Son called from the States.

46:24.573 --> 46:27.701
His son's having some trouble
adjusting to the school there.

46:27.910 --> 46:29.119
So he wants to come back.

46:30.245 --> 46:32.789
Does that mean I have to go right away?

46:33.165 --> 46:35.083
I thought you wanted to go
as soon as possible.

46:36.168 --> 46:37.753
Did you change your mind again?

46:38.712 --> 46:39.630
No.

46:48.805 --> 46:49.890
Bye.

46:50.474 --> 46:51.517
Isn't your flight at night?

46:53.477 --> 46:55.229
I'm going to have some fun before I leave.

47:01.026 --> 47:02.069
Jun-hui.

47:03.695 --> 47:05.906
Are you sure you can go to the States?

47:07.074 --> 47:08.158
What do you mean?

47:08.242 --> 47:10.160
You said your girlfriend
didn't agree to it yet.

47:11.703 --> 47:12.871
Just leave.

47:15.082 --> 47:16.124
See you.

47:32.975 --> 47:36.144
PERSONNEL APPOINTMENT

47:40.440 --> 47:41.942
JEONG YEONG-IN, PROMOTED

47:42.025 --> 47:44.653
CHOI JUNG-MO, PROMOTED
GEUM BO-RA, PROMOTED

47:44.736 --> 47:47.364
KIM DONG-U, PROMOTED
LEE YE-EUN, PROMOTED

47:47.447 --> 47:48.699
PERSONNEL TRANSFER AND PROMOTION

47:48.782 --> 47:51.660
YOON JIN-A, PROMOTED TO SECTION CHIEF
OF PAJU LOGISTICS CENTER

48:38.999 --> 48:41.960
Congratulations on your promotion.

48:42.210 --> 48:43.879
Stop acting like you're fine.

48:44.963 --> 48:45.964
Are you okay?

48:46.757 --> 48:49.259
That position you got
didn't even exist before.

48:49.551 --> 48:51.428
It's hard to see that as a promotion.

48:53.221 --> 48:54.306
I know that.

48:55.641 --> 48:56.767
And you're still smiling?

48:57.267 --> 48:58.894
Aren't you upset about it at all?

48:59.686 --> 49:02.773
Should I go to Mr. Jo's office
and throw a fit?

49:02.856 --> 49:06.693
He'll welcome that since he's dying
to blame something on you.

49:07.444 --> 49:08.612
That's why

49:08.987 --> 49:12.324
I'm going to endure everything
by working hard and staying quiet.

49:13.325 --> 49:16.078
People are going to think
that you're incredibly persistent.

49:16.870 --> 49:18.747
That's my goal.

49:21.208 --> 49:22.668
I'm proud of you.

49:23.794 --> 49:25.295
I learned it from you.

49:26.380 --> 49:29.716
You are far better than I am.
I'm impressed.

49:30.050 --> 49:31.968
I learned a lot from you.

49:32.052 --> 49:34.096
You know, I can do anything

49:34.179 --> 49:36.348
when I put my mind to it.

49:37.349 --> 49:39.226
Don't get too cocky now.

50:02.916 --> 50:05.043
Stop putting on an act.

50:05.877 --> 50:07.754
You can be happy about your promotion.

50:07.921 --> 50:09.965
You don't need to tiptoe around me.

50:10.382 --> 50:12.676
You are the one
who should stop putting on an act.

50:13.093 --> 50:15.262
To be honest,
you're getting punished, not promoted.

50:15.345 --> 50:16.847
You can sue them if you want to.

50:17.347 --> 50:20.851
I was expecting this much,
so I'm not even that surprised.

50:21.977 --> 50:24.730
Don't worry. I'll fight through

50:24.813 --> 50:27.065
and make an impressive come back.

50:27.149 --> 50:28.442
You know me.

50:29.359 --> 50:30.610
That's enough.

50:30.944 --> 50:33.238
Don't push yourself to change too quickly.

50:34.239 --> 50:35.949
I thought you liked it.

50:36.032 --> 50:37.868
I didn't know you'd go this far.

50:38.076 --> 50:40.495
You're so persistent.
You're unbelievably tough.

50:40.579 --> 50:43.331
Should I buy you
some congratulatory drinks?

50:43.915 --> 50:45.584
Shouldn't you meet Jun-hui
on your birthday?

50:45.959 --> 50:49.296
I have time. He has a meeting,
so we're going to meet later.

50:49.588 --> 50:53.091
Forget it. You can use that spare time
to doll yourself up.

50:54.050 --> 50:55.761
What are you talking about?

50:56.887 --> 50:58.263
- Who knows?
- What?

50:58.346 --> 51:01.308
You might've made a reservation
for a makeover in Gangnam.

51:01.850 --> 51:03.852
It's not our first night together.

51:04.227 --> 51:07.981
My gosh, does that mean...

51:09.775 --> 51:11.902
- Did you already...
- What are you saying?

51:12.611 --> 51:13.612
Thank you.

52:08.416 --> 52:11.044
Are hiccups contagious?

52:32.941 --> 52:34.359
They always make you drink too much.

52:47.038 --> 52:49.374
It reminded me of the day
we first held hands.

52:49.916 --> 52:52.085
You definitely made the first move on me.

52:58.049 --> 53:01.344
- Happy birthday to you
- Happy birthday to you

53:01.511 --> 53:04.598
- Happy birthday to you
- Happy birthday to you

53:05.223 --> 53:09.311
- Happy birthday, dear Jin-a
- Happy birthday, dear Jin-a

53:10.145 --> 53:13.315
- Happy birthday to you
- Happy birthday to you

53:20.113 --> 53:22.240
Happy birthday
and congratulations on your promotion.

53:22.449 --> 53:24.326
I'm so proud of you, Jin-a. You rock.

53:24.951 --> 53:26.244
Thanks, Dad.

53:27.454 --> 53:29.497
I guess your company is
full of incompetent employees.

53:29.664 --> 53:31.541
I can't believe they promoted you.

53:31.625 --> 53:33.001
Don't be rude to your sister.

53:33.501 --> 53:35.337
Do I have to say "Congratulations"?

53:35.420 --> 53:36.463
That's so uncool.

53:37.005 --> 53:39.841
Just admit that you're shy, okay?

53:42.177 --> 53:44.429
Shouldn't you be meeting Jun-hui
on a day like today?

53:47.349 --> 53:48.391
He has to work.

53:48.475 --> 53:49.726
Here, guys.

53:50.518 --> 53:52.479
You're a year older now,

53:52.562 --> 53:54.189
and you got promoted too.

53:54.272 --> 53:57.275
Now, you just have to meet a nice guy
and get married.

53:57.400 --> 54:00.153
A few Seoul National University graduates
from good families

54:00.236 --> 54:01.529
want to meet you.

54:01.655 --> 54:04.115
I'll pick the best one out of them

54:04.199 --> 54:06.076
and arrange a blind date for you.

54:06.326 --> 54:08.036
Here, cheers.

54:09.454 --> 54:10.455
Cheers, Jin-a.

54:20.006 --> 54:23.009
Don't even think about arguing with me
on this happy day.

54:23.093 --> 54:24.636
I won't change my mind anyway.

54:25.220 --> 54:27.013
I never tried to change your mind

54:28.098 --> 54:29.307
because I know it's impossible.

54:30.308 --> 54:31.685
But I've also made it clear to you.

54:32.185 --> 54:34.020
I will not change my mind either.

54:34.562 --> 54:36.106
You can't change my mind.

54:37.273 --> 54:39.401
Shut your mouth
before I start saying worse things.

54:39.484 --> 54:41.152
Enough already.

54:42.195 --> 54:43.947
You should eat, Jin-a.

54:45.365 --> 54:46.992
Have some shame, will you?

54:48.034 --> 54:50.954
You're seeing a guy who has nothing
to be proud of.

54:51.037 --> 54:52.414
How could you be so shameless?

54:52.956 --> 54:54.791
Do you know how important
family background is?

54:54.874 --> 54:57.085
It tells us how that person's future
will pan out.

54:57.168 --> 54:59.587
- Mom, please!
- You need to keep this in mind, too.

54:59.671 --> 55:00.797
I want you to cut ties

55:00.880 --> 55:02.882
with all the girls you know
before you get your PhD.

55:05.510 --> 55:07.345
If you're dragging this on, thinking that

55:07.429 --> 55:09.055
you'd be able to marry Jun-hui later on,

55:09.139 --> 55:10.348
you should give up now.

55:10.682 --> 55:12.434
I won't let him set foot in this house

55:12.517 --> 55:14.436
for the life of me.

55:21.651 --> 55:23.528
What? Are you leaving?

55:25.113 --> 55:27.782
Mom said she won't let Jun-hui
set foot in this house.

55:28.074 --> 55:29.367
What am I to do when I miss him?

55:29.451 --> 55:30.535
I should go see him.

55:32.495 --> 55:33.538
Jin-a.

55:34.914 --> 55:36.082
Jin-a.

55:43.423 --> 55:44.632
My gosh.

56:13.578 --> 56:15.455
The meeting is over. I'm on my way.

56:15.705 --> 56:17.874
Take your time and enjoy your meal
with your family.

56:18.625 --> 56:20.585
Should I drop you off
before we hit the main road?

56:20.919 --> 56:21.878
Yes.

56:28.176 --> 56:29.844
You can drop me off here.

57:09.050 --> 57:10.718
Something happened at home, right?

57:21.896 --> 57:23.022
You know my mom.

57:23.398 --> 57:24.941
Why? Did Jin-a say something?

57:38.705 --> 57:39.831
Did I keep you waiting long?

57:43.418 --> 57:45.253
This place is really nice.

58:23.791 --> 58:24.834
What is this?

58:26.169 --> 58:27.086
Happy birthday.

58:30.381 --> 58:31.424
Thanks.

58:48.483 --> 58:52.111
I GIVE ALL MY HEART TO YOU, JIN-A

59:32.485 --> 59:34.362
It's so beautiful.

59:41.786 --> 59:42.912
Do you like it?

59:44.747 --> 59:47.166
Yes, I love it so much.

01:00:24.621 --> 01:00:25.955
How is it? Does it look good?

01:00:28.041 --> 01:00:28.916
Obviously,

01:00:29.917 --> 01:00:31.377
it's not as beautiful as you are.

01:01:07.038 --> 01:01:08.081
I must say,

01:01:09.749 --> 01:01:12.543
the fact that this makes me so happy...

01:01:13.670 --> 01:01:17.340
makes me realize
that I'm so materialistic.

01:01:18.257 --> 01:01:19.801
It's really beautiful.

01:01:21.844 --> 01:01:23.054
It looks great on you.

01:01:23.680 --> 01:01:24.722
Thanks.

01:02:47.180 --> 01:02:48.681
Thanks for today.

01:02:59.942 --> 01:03:01.569
The process was quite unpleasant,

01:03:01.944 --> 01:03:03.237
but I did get promoted.

01:03:03.321 --> 01:03:04.989
Aren't you going to
congratulate me on that?

01:03:10.244 --> 01:03:11.746
I don't want to force you.

01:03:12.914 --> 01:03:16.709
To tell you the truth,
I'm annoyed by it as well.

01:03:17.043 --> 01:03:19.837
I guess they want me to suffer,
but I'm not scared.

01:03:20.713 --> 01:03:23.925
I'm going to show them
how tenacious and persistent I can be.

01:03:27.220 --> 01:03:28.679
I'll be going to the States soon.

01:03:38.981 --> 01:03:39.857
Come with me.

01:03:44.111 --> 01:03:47.031
I'm not asking you to forget about
what needs to be resolved at work.

01:03:48.991 --> 01:03:50.576
They need to be reprimanded.

01:03:51.077 --> 01:03:54.580
But you don't have to stay here for that,
you know.

01:04:00.044 --> 01:04:01.712
I know there are many things stopping you.

01:04:03.214 --> 01:04:05.466
That's why I was hesitant to ask you this,

01:04:06.676 --> 01:04:07.718
and I feel bad too.

01:04:10.221 --> 01:04:14.058
I know everyone will think that you're
running away from the situation,

01:04:14.559 --> 01:04:15.893
and it'll hurt your pride.

01:04:17.061 --> 01:04:18.104
But...

01:04:20.064 --> 01:04:21.148
I'm just going to ignore it.

01:04:23.943 --> 01:04:26.028
I can no longer watch you suffer.

01:04:41.043 --> 01:04:42.086
Let's leave...

01:04:43.713 --> 01:04:44.714
together.

01:05:16.120 --> 01:05:17.246
If it was the old me,

01:05:18.748 --> 01:05:20.291
I probably would have...

01:05:23.044 --> 01:05:25.296
left with you in a heartbeat

01:05:28.299 --> 01:05:30.092
even if you were leaving right now.

01:05:33.638 --> 01:05:35.348
I really would have.

01:05:41.687 --> 01:05:42.855
But you see...

01:05:45.107 --> 01:05:46.359
I think I have...

01:05:51.781 --> 01:05:53.324
matured too much to do so.

01:05:58.996 --> 01:06:00.164
You turned me...

01:06:02.124 --> 01:06:04.627
into a real grown-up.

01:07:12.737 --> 01:07:14.071
Get home safely.

01:07:33.758 --> 01:07:35.176
You really can't come with me?

01:07:45.686 --> 01:07:46.854
I'm sorry.

01:12:12.119 --> 01:12:13.787
Hello.

01:12:14.204 --> 01:12:15.372
Thank you.

01:12:15.456 --> 01:12:16.457
Bye.

01:12:32.181 --> 01:12:37.770
SAVE THE DATE FOR OUR WEDDING
APRIL 28TH, 2018

01:12:38.228 --> 01:12:42.232
GROOM: YOON SEUNG-HO
BRIDE: KIM HUI-WON

01:12:56.080 --> 01:12:58.540
What brings the busy restaurant owner
to call me?

01:12:58.749 --> 01:13:00.584
I got the wedding invitation.

01:13:01.001 --> 01:13:03.337
- Did you get it?
- Yes.

01:13:03.587 --> 01:13:05.422
I sent it to you because you asked for it,

01:13:05.506 --> 01:13:07.091
but you don't need to come.

01:13:08.092 --> 01:13:10.260
It's my brother's wedding.
You don't need to be there.

01:13:10.344 --> 01:13:11.595
Plus, it's so far away.

01:13:12.346 --> 01:13:14.807
I'm going there to see you.

01:13:15.682 --> 01:13:19.686
How does it feel to have your brother
get married before you?

01:13:21.397 --> 01:13:23.565
I'm pretty calm about it.

01:13:24.191 --> 01:13:25.401
Don't lie to me.

01:13:27.027 --> 01:13:28.529
Am I supposed to cry?

01:13:29.405 --> 01:13:31.323
Are you sure you're totally fine with it?

01:13:32.699 --> 01:13:35.869
Things like this don't upset me anymore.

01:13:37.746 --> 01:13:39.081
You sound like an old lady.

01:13:40.290 --> 01:13:43.168
We'll be turning 40 soon!

01:13:43.252 --> 01:13:45.421
Gosh, let's hang up.
I'll see you at the wedding.

01:13:45.504 --> 01:13:47.381
- My gosh.
- See you.

01:14:19.621 --> 01:14:21.331
How gorgeous.

01:14:23.834 --> 01:14:26.211
Look at the sky. It's gorgeous.

01:14:33.343 --> 01:14:35.387
It's so pretty. Look at it.

01:14:36.430 --> 01:14:37.473
Look.

01:14:38.182 --> 01:14:40.476
- I'm looking.
- What are you looking at?

01:14:40.684 --> 01:14:41.894
I told you to look at the sky.

01:14:42.644 --> 01:14:44.771
Look at the sky, not me.

01:14:44.855 --> 01:14:46.190
You're prettier.

01:14:47.524 --> 01:14:48.775
That's a given.

01:14:50.027 --> 01:14:51.320
I know.

01:14:52.196 --> 01:14:53.238
What's wrong with you?

01:14:54.406 --> 01:14:55.824
What's up with the compliment?

01:14:56.241 --> 01:14:57.451
Are you sick?

01:15:00.412 --> 01:15:01.455
I'm just stating the truth.

01:15:05.334 --> 01:15:06.710
There are so many people around.

01:16:14.736 --> 01:16:17.531
- Thank you for coming.
- Congratulations.

01:16:17.614 --> 01:16:21.201
Microphone test. One, two, three.

01:16:21.910 --> 01:16:24.788
One, two, three.

01:16:26.331 --> 01:16:27.749
I'd like to make an announcement.

01:16:27.833 --> 01:16:30.377
I'd like to ask the guests to come inside.

01:16:31.503 --> 01:16:36.883
The groom's guests can sit on the right.
The bride's can sit on the left.

01:16:37.467 --> 01:16:39.344
The wedding ceremony will begin soon.

01:16:39.428 --> 01:16:41.305
So I'd like the guests

01:16:41.513 --> 01:16:44.057
to come inside
and start taking their seats.

01:16:47.561 --> 01:16:49.855
Stop. I knew it.

01:16:49.938 --> 01:16:52.691
- Ms. Geum, it's been so long.
- My gosh.

01:16:52.774 --> 01:16:53.859
- Hey.
- She's my daughter.

01:16:53.942 --> 01:16:56.028
I can't believe you have a daughter.

01:16:56.612 --> 01:16:58.196
She's such a handful.

01:16:58.280 --> 01:16:59.740
Come here. Let me hold you.

01:17:00.324 --> 01:17:02.451
Then give her to me. I'll take her.

01:17:02.659 --> 01:17:04.661
- Go ahead.
- Do you want to live with me?

01:17:05.287 --> 01:17:07.581
- Goodness.
- Why are you so cute?

01:17:09.458 --> 01:17:11.668
- She doesn't like you.
- Do you want to go to your mom?

01:17:12.252 --> 01:17:13.879
- How's your wife doing?
- She's fine.

01:17:14.338 --> 01:17:15.505
- Thank you.
- Hey.

01:17:15.589 --> 01:17:17.924
Hello. Thank you for coming.

01:17:24.890 --> 01:17:25.891
Hello.

01:17:26.933 --> 01:17:28.185
How have you been?

01:17:33.523 --> 01:17:35.484
- Hello.
- When are you going to get married?

01:17:35.567 --> 01:17:37.277
Your mom's so worried about you.

01:17:37.361 --> 01:17:38.695
You should hurry up.

01:17:38.779 --> 01:17:40.697
Are you seeing anyone?
Should I set you up?

01:17:40.781 --> 01:17:43.283
She has a boyfriend,
but she's not getting married.

01:17:43.408 --> 01:17:44.409
Really?

01:17:44.576 --> 01:17:46.745
Then why aren't you getting married?

01:17:46.953 --> 01:17:49.581
- You're only getting older.
- I know.

01:17:50.040 --> 01:17:51.875
Your brother's getting married before you.

01:17:51.958 --> 01:17:53.543
- Don't smile like you're fine.
- Exactly.

01:17:53.627 --> 01:17:55.921
- You should get married as well.
- She's right.

01:17:56.838 --> 01:17:57.839
Enjoy.

01:18:01.843 --> 01:18:02.844
I know.

01:18:03.929 --> 01:18:05.681
No, I'll take care of it.

01:18:10.644 --> 01:18:12.187
I'll be right there.

01:18:12.604 --> 01:18:15.357
Yes, meet me at the airport.
Bring your passport.

01:18:15.440 --> 01:18:17.859
Yes, okay. Bye.

01:18:19.569 --> 01:18:20.779
My gosh.

01:18:21.697 --> 01:18:24.449
I kind of overheard.
Is it an urgent business trip?

01:18:25.575 --> 01:18:28.537
I told you about the slow deal
going on in Hong Kong, right?

01:18:28.662 --> 01:18:30.956
They suddenly want to sign the contract.

01:18:31.081 --> 01:18:32.708
I should go before they change their mind.

01:18:33.041 --> 01:18:36.044
So you're just going to miss the wedding?

01:18:37.170 --> 01:18:38.338
My flight...

01:18:42.008 --> 01:18:43.051
Okay.

01:18:43.927 --> 01:18:44.970
Sorry.

01:18:46.930 --> 01:18:49.474
Shouldn't I talk to your parents
before I leave?

01:18:50.142 --> 01:18:52.477
They're probably really busy.

01:18:52.602 --> 01:18:54.604
Then can you say goodbye to them for me?

01:18:54.688 --> 01:18:55.772
Just a second.

01:18:56.148 --> 01:18:57.524
Hello?

01:18:58.859 --> 01:18:59.860
Yes.

01:19:00.861 --> 01:19:02.154
The terms will stay the same.

01:19:02.821 --> 01:19:05.407
Of course.
Tell them we'll comply with everything.

01:19:05.490 --> 01:19:07.409
That's the only way
we can make them sign it.

01:19:07.492 --> 01:19:08.493
Yes.

01:19:09.077 --> 01:19:10.078
Yes.

01:19:10.996 --> 01:19:12.622
Okay. Bye.

01:19:14.541 --> 01:19:16.168
Can you stop frowning at me like that?

01:19:16.460 --> 01:19:19.045
I need to go.
It's a really important contract.

01:19:19.588 --> 01:19:20.422
You know that.

01:19:21.465 --> 01:19:23.133
Okay, fine. You should go.

01:19:24.384 --> 01:19:26.011
I promise I'll get you an expensive gift.

01:19:29.681 --> 01:19:30.849
Hello?

01:19:31.475 --> 01:19:33.560
Yes, I know.

01:19:34.644 --> 01:19:36.021
Yes.

01:19:38.523 --> 01:19:39.816
Why is that important?

01:19:41.109 --> 01:19:43.153
There's no need to worry about that. Okay.

01:19:43.236 --> 01:19:45.238
I'll see you there. I'm going now. Bye.

01:19:46.656 --> 01:19:48.575
I really need to go. I'll call you.

01:19:51.828 --> 01:19:52.662
Hello?

01:19:56.833 --> 01:19:58.543
Yes. Hello?

01:20:16.561 --> 01:20:18.104
Jun-hui, long time no see.

01:20:18.188 --> 01:20:19.564
- Hey.
- How have you been?

01:20:19.648 --> 01:20:21.566
- Look who it is.
- When did you get here?

01:20:21.650 --> 01:20:22.609
- Just now.
- Let's go.

01:20:22.692 --> 01:20:25.028
- Okay.
- You look great.

01:20:25.111 --> 01:20:27.197
You haven't aged at all.

01:20:27.697 --> 01:20:30.200
You must have had so much fun
in the States.

01:21:24.254 --> 01:21:25.630
But when I saw him,

01:21:26.214 --> 01:21:28.300
it felt like I was with him
just until yesterday.

01:21:28.383 --> 01:21:31.636
I would've run over and hugged him.

01:21:31.845 --> 01:21:35.640
But do you know what I kept thinking
when I was in the States?

01:21:36.141 --> 01:21:39.269
I kept wishing
that Jin-a wouldn't be that happy.

01:21:39.352 --> 01:21:41.521
It sounds like
you still have feelings for her.

01:21:41.605 --> 01:21:43.356
Jin-a, you'll get yourself in trouble.

01:21:43.440 --> 01:21:46.109
Are you saying
you're going to start over with her?

01:21:46.192 --> 01:21:47.694
Can you really be around me

01:21:48.194 --> 01:21:50.155
as if nothing has ever happened
between us?

01:21:50.739 --> 01:21:52.532
After a certain moment,

01:21:53.116 --> 01:21:54.826
I tried to think of it this way.

01:21:55.327 --> 01:21:59.205
That was the furthest
our relationship could go.

01:22:00.206 --> 01:22:02.792
That was the best we could do.

01:22:05.587 --> 01:22:07.881
Subtitle translation by Kim Su-hyeon
